eTaste</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 8:15:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bad idea</span><hr size=1> First of all thats a bad idea. Ill tell you why. Critcal hits actually become a spam in themselves. They are actually pretty damn annoying if you ask me. Get a big raid going and you get line after line of text with critical hits. Heaven forbid the tanks use their discs. Now just imagine all that spam PLUS the casters damage? I for one dont want or need that. Yes you can make an option to turn it off, but even still, if you need to turn it off why have it?  Would be interesting in group situations for exp, but still. Do you want  tank_00 to see Eelienu nukes a froglock dar knight for 10 points of damage! Sad thing is, at lvl 60 I still get partial resists /sigh. <br>
<br>
They game doesnt really need this. What it needs is balancing. Showing people how much damage we do isnt really a big deal. They dont care how much damage we do in a short period of time, they care about sustaining the damage over a long fight. We cant do that. With the new pets in Luclin, we should be working towards that. <br>
<br>
If you look in the class balancing under &quot;Wizard pets are now known&quot; (i think thats it) there is a possible description of the pets there. I believe that to be nearly true though i doubt they shout to the zone lol. I have also heard from a friend that the pets will be damn close to the description there.  <br>
<br>
